cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper presents a method applicable to UWB networks for person detection and ranging.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper may discuss security implications of detecting and ranging people in a network.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is possible as the paper may discuss the information content of the signals used for detection and ranging.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible as the paper may discuss applications of the method in multimedia systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is possible as the paper may discuss the control of the UWB infrastructure for person detection and ranging.
